   "source": [
    "# AI-Driven Student Performance Prediction System\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook reproduces the complete machine learning workflow for the student pass/fail prediction system. It is designed for project review, portfolio demonstration, and academic submission."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Workflow Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "```mermaid\n",
    "flowchart TD\n",
    "    A[Dataset] --> B[Data Cleaning]\n",
    "    B --> C[Preprocessing]\n",
    "    C --> D[EDA]\n",
    "    D --> E[Feature Engineering]\n",
    "    E --> F[Train/Test Split]\n",
    "    F --> G[Model Comparison]\n",
    "    G --> H[Best Model]\n",
    "    H --> I[Prediction]\n",
    "    I --> J[Streamlit Dashboard]\n",
    "```\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Environment Setup\n",
    "\n",
  
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path.cwd().parents[0] if Path.cwd().name == 'notebooks' else Path.cwd()\n",
    "if str(PROJECT_ROOT) not in sys.path:\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT))\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.config import FIGURES_DIR, PROCESSED_DATA_DIR, REPORTS_DIR, ensure_directories\n",
    "from src.data_preprocessing import clean_student_data, load_student_data, split_features_target\n",
    "from src.eda import run_eda\n",
    "from src.predict import predict_student\n",
    "from src.train import train_and_select_model\n",
    "\n",
    "ensure_directories()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "The loader automatically combines Mathematics and Portuguese course files when both are available."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_df = load_student_data()\n",
    "raw_df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_df.shape, raw_df.columns.tolist()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Data Cleaning and Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "The final grade `G3` is converted into a binary target. `G3` is then excluded from features in the training pipeline to avoid target leakage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cleaned_df = clean_student_data(raw_df)\n",
    "cleaned_df.to_csv(PROCESSED_DATA_DIR / 'student_performance_processed.csv', index=False)\n",
    "cleaned_df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cleaned_df['pass'].value_counts().rename({0: 'Fail', 1: 'Pass'})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Exploratory Data Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "EDA figures are generated automatically and saved to `../outputs/figures/`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "run_eda(cleaned_df)\n",
    "sorted(path.name for path in FIGURES_DIR.glob('*.png'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cleaned_df.describe().T"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Feature and Target Split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X, y = split_features_target(cleaned_df)\n",
    "print(f'Feature matrix: {X.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'Target vector: {y.shape}')\n",
    "X.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Model Comparison and Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "The training pipeline compares Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, and Support Vector Machine. The best model is selected using ROC-AUC, with accuracy as a tie-breaker."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "best_model, comparison_df = train_and_select_model()\n",
    "comparison_df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Generated Evaluation Artifacts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pd.read_csv(REPORTS_DIR / 'model_comparison.csv')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print((REPORTS_DIR / 'classification_report.txt').read_text())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Expected visual outputs:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `correlation_heatmap.png`\n",
    "- `feature_importance.png`\n",
    "- `confusion_matrix.png`\n",
    "- `roc_curve.png`\n",
    "- `precision_recall_curve.png`\n",
    "- `class_distribution.png`\n",
    "- `model_accuracy_comparison.png`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Single Student Prediction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
